</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,690,933]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
Note: According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Mielke, C. G. C." box="[374,657,799,825]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref8808" refString="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Mielke, C. G. C. (2019) Two new species of Palpifer Hampson, 1893 from South East Asia (Lepidoptera: Hepialidae). Bishop Museum Occasional Papers, 125, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="2019">Grehan &amp; Mielke (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1968" box="[669,784,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Palpifer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falkneri">
<emphasis box="[669,784,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">P. falkneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed only in 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1101,799,825]" name="Nepal" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, though the status of this species was claimed to be geographically near northeastern species. They also added 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1968" box="[1123,1238,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Palpifer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falkneri">
<emphasis box="[1123,1238,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">P. falkneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Indian species in abstract of their paper. Due to paucity of literatures of the Indian distribution of this species, this has not been placed in this catalogue.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
